{"word":"H2091 - זָהָב - zâhâb - zaw-hawb' - Gold","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>மூல வார்த்தை / Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">זָהָב</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>எழுத்துமாற்றம் / Transliteration: </strong>zâhâb"},{"paragraph":"<strong>ஒலிபெயர்ப்பு / Phonetic: </strong>zaw-hawb'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>சுருக்க விளக்கம் / Short Definition: </strong>Gold"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"பொன், தங்கம் - ஆண்பால் பெயர்ச்சொல்"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"gold, as a measure of weight, used of brilliance, splendor (figurative)"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"spacer\"></span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"parts-of-speech\"><strong>Part(s) of speech:</strong> Noun Masculine / பெயர்ச்சொல் (ஆண்பால்)</span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"spacer\"></span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"original-in-english\"><strong>ஆங்கில மூலம் / Original in English:</strong> From an unused root meaning to <i>shimmer</i>; <i>gold</i>; figuratively something <i>gold colored</i> (that is, <i>yellow</i>), as <i>oil</i>, a <i>clear sky: - </i>gold (-en), fair weather."},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"spacer\"></span>"}]}